<h2 data-start="3900" data-end="3939" class=""><strong data-start="3903" data-end="3939">🔗 Relationships in the Database</strong></h2>
<ul data-start="3940" data-end="4356">
<li data-start="3940" data-end="4042" class="">
<p data-start="3942" data-end="4042" class=""><strong data-start="3942" data-end="3957">One-to-Many</strong>: One instructor can create multiple courses (<code data-start="4003" data-end="4018">instructor_id</code> in the course table).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4043" data-end="4155" class="">
<p data-start="4045" data-end="4155" class=""><strong data-start="4045" data-end="4061">Many-to-Many</strong>: Students can enroll in multiple courses (<code data-start="4104" data-end="4116">enrollment</code> table bridges students and courses).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4156" data-end="4253" class="">
<p data-start="4158" data-end="4253" class=""><strong data-start="4158" data-end="4173">One-to-Many</strong>: Each course contains multiple lessons (<code data-start="4214" data-end="4222">lesson</code> table links to <code data-start="4238" data-end="4249">course_id</code>).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4254" data-end="4356" class="">
